FBIS3-34738 "drnes030_s_94006" FBIS-NES-94-030 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Feb 1994 Iran New Director General Appointed LD1302112294 Tehran IRNA in English 1022 GMT 13 Feb 94 LD1302112294 Tehran IRNA Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tehran, Feb. 13, IRNA -- Leader of the Islamic Revolution Ayatollah 'Ali Khamene'i appointed 'Ali Larijani to the post of director general of the Islamic Republic of Iran Broadcasting (IRIB) here Sunday. The appointment was made for a period of five years. Larijani was also appointed as the member of the High Council of the Cultural Revolution. Larijani who, prior to his new assingment served as the minister of culture and islamic guidance, replaces Mohammad Hashemi who run IRIB for 13 years.
